The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Monday, November 04, 2002 				 Osama wife, son held
																								London, Nov. 3 (Agencies): Iranian security forces have detained one of Osama bin Ladens sons among several hundred people suspected of links to the al-Qaida terror network, The Financial Times reported. 																								His youngest wife was also arrested after a gun battle at her fathers compound in Yemen. Amal al-Saddah, Ladens fifth and favourite wife, who is in her early twenties, has been placed under house arrest and questioned by Yemeni authorities, The Sunday Times reported.
